I took a little (and I mean little) poll recently on Oscar ringleader and staunch Jamie Foxx-supporter Chris Rock. I asked this of a coupla famous performers: &ldquo;Should a major Awards emcee be impartial or not?&rdquo;
Jorja Fox of CSI: &ldquo;Yes. But I think that folks should be good-humored about hosts making jokes and things.&rdquo;

[&hellip;]
Mark also catches up with JORJA FOX, who reveals, &ldquo;This is my favorite set on the show. It is a graphic, gruesome place.&rdquo;
Jorja also fills Mark in that no animals or insects have ever been hurt on the show. They are under the protection of a Humane Society representative who makes sure they are well taken care of and that they recently switched the company that supplies their gloves.
